==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wany
<hw>Wan"y</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Waning or diminished in
some parts; not of uniform size throughout; -- said especially of sawed
boards or timber when tapering or uneven, from being cut too near the
outside of the log.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Spoiled by wet; -- said of timber.</def>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wanze</ent>⟦br⟧
